Biography - James O'Hern

James O'Hern, Secretary of State of Illinois, and ex-officio Superintendent of Public Instruction, is among the leading men of the Prairie State. Born near Lawrence, Kansas, October 21, 1852, he spent his boyhood on the home farm and attended the public schools. He completed his education at Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland, where he took his degree in 1874, winning the gold medal for essay writing. After graduation Mr. O'Hern began his business career as a teacher in the public schools of Chicago. In 1881 he was appointed Superintendent of Chicago Police, under Mayor Harrison. Mr. O'Hern brought to that office a ripe experience with men and affairs, and a training which he bent to the service of the city with most gratifying results. The same year he was elected Sheriff of Cook County, and was re-elected in 1884. In 1887 he was again a candidato for Mayor of Chicago. In 1889 Mr. O'Hern was named a member of the Democratic National Committee, and in 1890 was appointed Collector of the Port of Chicago. He was a prominent candidate for Secretary of State at the State Convention of 1892, and was elected to that position the following year. He was a delegate to the National Democratic Convention in 1896, and is at this writing (1900) a prominent candidate for Mayor of Chicago. Mr. O'Hern possesses many of the qualities which go to make up a great political leader. He is a logical and forceful thinker, and he knows how to express his thoughts clearly and forcibly. He is possessed of a rare gift of oratory. He has a thorough training and fine scholarship, and is a man of delightful social qualities. Mr. O'Hern is the author of several books. In 1887 he published "The Irish in America," a work which attracted much attention and was severely criticised by certain organs of the Ancient Order of Hibernians. In the same year appeared "The Other Side," in which the author replied to his critics. He also wrote a life of William O'Brien, the Irish patriot. Mr. O'Hern possesses a pleasing personality and is an entertaining writer. He is a man of large intellectual ability, and a student of men and affairs. He is a forceful speaker, and is popular alike in public and private life.

You probably hear it a lot: install Analytics, Optimize and Tag Manager, make sure you implement Google Search Console and also set up your Google My Business profile. It‚Äôs a mouth full and also a lot of work. What exactly is in it for you and how do you make the most of it?

Why Google tools?

If you do digital marketing for a small business or work for a small business, you might feel it‚Äôs hard to compete with the large companies. Big players like Amazon, large retail chains and service providers do a lot of digital marketing and have way more resources than you. Google provides you with a lot of tools that will help you to increase your online visibility and compete with the big players. They also provide you with tools to improve your understanding of your customers and their behavior on your website.

The importance of analytics

If you don‚Äôt measure your results, you don‚Äôt know what works and what does not. Without insights, you will not be able to improve your website or marketing campaigns. Google Analytics provides you with a lot of insights into the behavior of the visitors of your website. This way you can find out how they found your site, what pages they visited and how long they stayed on your website. You can also find out what devices they‚Äôre using, which country they‚Äôre in and a lot of other data.

Improve your website

These insights can be used to improve your website and marketing campaigns. For example, you can find out which pages are performing well and which ones need to be improved. Also, you can find out which channels are driving the most traffic to your website and adjust your ad spend accordingly.

Optimize your website

Google Optimize is a tool that helps you to test different versions of your website. You can create different variations of a page, such as a different headline or a different call to action (CTA), and then test them against each other. This way you can find out which version performs best and increase your conversion rate.

Find out more about your customers

Besides the data Google Analytics provides about the behavior of the visitors of your website, Google My Business provides you with insights into who your customers are. The insights are based on demographic data collected by Google. For example, you can find out the age, gender and interests of your customers. This data can be used to create more targeted marketing campaigns.

People find you

People can find your business online by searching for it in the Google search engine. Google Search Console provides you with insights into how people are finding your website. You can find out which keywords they‚Äôre using, which pages they‚Äôre visiting and which countries they‚Äôre in. This data can be used to improve your website‚Äôs ranking in the search results.

The importance of structured data

Structured data is a way to organize the information on your website so that Google can understand it better. This will help Google to display your website in the search results and can also lead to rich snippets. Rich snippets are extra pieces of information that are shown in the search results, such as reviews or prices. By using Google‚Äôs tools, you can improve your website, optimize your marketing campaigns and find out more about your customers. This can lead to more leads, more sales and more website traffic. I take it you mean with powdered butter? As in the kind you can get in the dairy section? 

From my understanding when I dipped my toes into it a few years ago, you can just add it as an ingredient. It's just a dehydrated form of butter after all. It can be rehydrated with water or milk then added as an ingredient. 

As for the amount...well, that depends on the recipe. If you're just adding it to a batter or dough, you could use a 1:1 ratio of powdered butter to regular butter. So if a recipe calls for 1 cup of butter, you could use 1 cup of powdered butter and 1 cup of water or milk.

As for baking with it? Well, I've never done that so I can't really say. I imagine it would be similar to using butter, but you might have to adjust the amount of liquid you use.

Ultimately, the best way to find out how to use powdered butter is to experiment. Start with a small amount and see how it affects the recipe. You can always add more, but it's hard to take it away!

Core Graphics resources and what should I do to programmatically measure a PDF document?

I am trying to measure the left, top, right, and bottom of a PDF document. I am trying to do this with Core Graphics. I am able to get the current dimensions of the page I am on, but I am not sure what resource I am supposed to use to find the PDF document's dimensions. I know the PDF document is larger than the page, so how do I find the dimensions of the entire document? Does anyone know what I am supposed to do? [Answer 1] In order to measure the whole document you need to use the CGPDFDocumentGetMediaBox function. It returns the media box for the whole document (which is the region that shall contain all the pages). You should also take in consideration that a PDF document can have a crop box which may be smaller than the media box. It's the region of the MediaBox (MediaBox is the boundary of the whole document) that will actually be printed, displayed or used as the film negative. To get it, you can use the CGPDFDocumentGetCropBox function. You can also use different boxes, depending on what information you need. Here is a list of all the boxes that are supported by Core Graphics. For each type of box you can get the width and the height with CGRectGetWidth and CGRectGetHeight respectively. [Answer 2] I am working with raster graphics, so I don't know how much this will help, but I used the code below to draw the CGPDFPage to a Core Graphics context, and then I could get the size of the context, which is the size of the page: CGContextRef context = CGBitmapContextCreate(NULL, width, height, 8, width * 4, CGColorSpaceCreateDeviceRGB(), kCGBitmapByteOrderDefault | kCGImageAlphaPremultipliedFirst); CGPDFPageRef page = CGPDFDocumentGetPage(_pdfDocument, pageNumber); CGContextDrawPDFPage(context, page);

Thomas Lewis (1881‚Äì1945) was a British cardiologist. He was born in Cardiff on 18 December 1881. Initially he studied at the University of Wales College of Medicine in Cardiff but after graduating in 1904 he continued studying in London where he became a member of the Royal College of Physicians in 1907 and a fellow in 1918. In 1912 he was appointed assistant physician at the University College Hospital in London. During World War I he served in the Royal Army Medical Corps in Egypt and Salonika. After the war he continued working at the University College Hospital. He became full physician in 1921 and physician-in-charge from 1922 to 1937. In 1937 he was appointed director of the Clinical Research Unit at the Medical Research Council of the UK. Lewis is chiefly remembered for his work on electrocardiography and angina pectoris. He published nearly 200 papers on various subjects including heart murmurs, coronary artery disease, and paroxysmal tachycardia. Of special note is his 1935 paper which proposed the term "effort angina" to describe angina pectoris precipitated by physical exertion. He died on 17 April 1945.

LUCILLE GRAVES OBITUARY

Graves, Lucille C. WEST SAND LAKE Lucille C. Graves, 96 of West Sand Lake, died on Sunday, February 26, 2012 at St. Peter's Hospice Inn. Born in Troy on December 10, 1915, she was the daughter of the late Frank and Helen (Sullivan) Carey. She was raised in West Sand Lake and was a resident for most of her life. Lucille was a graduate of Troy High School and was a homemaker. Loving and devoted mother of Henry F. (Barbara) Graves of Averill Park, Lucille M. (Joseph) White of Poestenkill, Mary Louise (Francis) White of Colonie, Elizabeth A. (Michael) Dougherty of Colonie, Lawrence J. (Lillian) Graves of Poestenkill, Helene A. Graves of West Sand Lake, Robert J. (Margaret) Graves of Binghamton, Patricia H. (Robert) DiBacco of West Yarmouth, Mass. and John W. (Linda) Graves of Broadalbin. Dear grandmother of 30 grandchildren, 48 great-grandchildren and seven great-great-grandchildren. Sister of the late Clara DeGraff, Helen Dineen and Gerald Carey. Also survived by several nieces and nephews. Funeral service will be held on Thursday at 9:45 a.m. at the John H. Clinton Funeral Home, 346 4th St. Watervliet and at 10:30 a.m. at Sacred Heart of Mary Church, West Sand Lake where the Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated. Calling hours will be on Wednesday from 4 to 8 p.m. Interment St. Agnes Cemetery, Menands. Contributions may be made to St. Peter's Hospice Inn, 315 S. Manning Blvd., Albany, NY 12208 or Community Hospice, 445 New Karner Road, Albany NY 12205-3119.

The Story of Kisho's Red Velvet

Once upon a time, in a small town nestled amidst rolling hills, lived a baker named Kisho who had an extraordinary passion for creating delicious treats. One crisp winter morning, as the sun cast golden rays upon the town, Kisho awoke with a sudden inspiration. He had always wanted to create something unique and magical‚Äîa cake that would leave people spellbound with its flavors and beauty. Driven by his passion, Kisho began experimenting with new ingredients and techniques in his cozy bakery. After countless trials and errors, he finally stumbled upon a divine masterpiece‚Äîthe Kisho's Red Velvet. This magnificent cake was an instant success, winning the hearts of the townspeople with its velvety soft texture, vibrant red hue, and a symphony of flavors that danced on the palate. The secret behind Kisho's Red Velvet lay in the perfect balance of cocoa powder and buttermilk, which gave the cake its unique moistness and tanginess. The deep red color came from pure beet juice, carefully added to preserve the cake's natural sweetness. Layers of creamy cream cheese frosting, swirled between the red velvet layers, completed the masterpiece, elevating it to a work of art that captivated the senses. Word of Kisho's Red Velvet spread like wildfire throughout the town. People came from far and wide to taste this delectable creation, and the bakery became a destination of joy and celebration. Kisho's Red Velvet found its way to birthdays, weddings, anniversaries, and all occasions that deserved a touch of magic. As time went on, Kisho's Red Velvet became a symbol of love, happiness, and unity. The vibrant red color represented passion and joy, while the velvety texture and sweet flavors brought people together, creating moments of pure bliss. The cake became a symbol of Kisho's dedication and passion for his craft, a testament to the transformative power of a simple creation. Kisho's Red Velvet left an indelible mark on the town and its people. It was more than just a cake; it was a symbol of creativity, love, and the beauty that can be found in everyday moments. And so, the story of Kisho's Red Velvet was passed down from generation to generation, inspiring bakers and dessert enthusiasts to create their own magical culinary wonders, spreading joy and sweetness wherever they went.

David Mullins believes he was "lucky" to escape serious injury after crashing in an event at Wincanton on Sunday.

The champion jump jockey remained conscious after his mount Genuflex failed to take off at the fourth fence and somersaulted, unseating Mullins in the process.

The 29-year-old's helmet came off but the severity of the incident has not deterred Mullins, who intends to ride again later this week.

He told the Daily Mail: "I'm lucky, I got a bit of a bang to the head but I feel fine today. It's all part of the job.

"I somehow kept my wits about me, I can't really explain it. It happened so quickly. I was in no pain and I was aware of everything that was going on.

"I don't feel any different and I'm looking forward to going back racing on Wednesday. Hopefully I'm not as sore as I thought I was going to be."

It is not the first time Mullins has endured a serious fall, having sustained a fractured skull in a point-to-point race at Ballindenisk in 2014.

He added: "This was different. The one I had before was probably a bit more serious. I have been lucky in that I haven't had too many bad falls.

"I just have to concentrate on what I have to do and that's go racing. I'm fine, I'll get back on another horse and forget about it."

A Report from the MAY 2006 General Meeting of the Colorado Springs Astronomy Club

by Michael Hardiman
The May meeting was moved up one week and was held on the 11th to allow the program speaker to get back to Pennsylvania before his school year ended. CSAC meetings are normally held on the third Thursday of every month. There were only 38 members and 6 guests in attendance for this month's meeting. Thanks to John Vincent there were 2 new members. Jim Bartol (a long-time friend of CSAC) and his son Eric joined us. We hope to see more of them at future meetings. Club vice president Craig Eichhorn called the meeting to order at 7:30 pm. Minutes from the April meeting were read and approved. Craig then announced that the club had received an Electronic Project Grant from the Astronomical League. The grant will pay for the purchase of a new computer and software for the Catoctin Mountain Observing Station. The hardware and software will be delivered and installed before the end of June. Craig provided updates on the status of several other club projects: * The annual CSAC Star Party will be held on August 18 and 19 at the Double Diamond Ranch, near Calhan. The event will be open to the public from 7:00 pm until midnight on Friday and from 1:00 pm until midnight on Saturday. Further details will be available later this summer. * The club is planning to hold two astronomy courses at Colorado Springs Community College during the Fall 2006 semester. The first course will provide a general introduction to astronomy and the second will be a more advanced course that will cover topics such as stellar evolution and cosmology. More information about the courses will be available on the CSCC website within the next few months. * The club is planning to hold a weekend astronomy workshop at the Double Diamond Ranch on September 16 and 17. The workshop will cover topics such as telescope basics, astrophotography, and deep sky observing. More information about the workshop will be available later this summer. * The club is planning to participate in the 2006 National Science Festival, which will be held in Washington, D.C., on October 7 and 8. The club will have a booth at the festival where we will be distributing information about astronomy and the club. Craig then congratulated John Vincent on his election as president of the Astronomical League. John will officially take office on July 1. After a break for snacks, Jim Crawford introduced the program speaker, Dr. Michael Brotherton, an astronomer from the University of Wyoming. Dr. Brotherton's talk was entitled "Witness to Cosmic Evolution: What Active Galaxies Can Tell Us about the Early Universe." Dr. Brotherton began his talk by explaining the difference between active galaxies and normal galaxies. Active galaxies are galaxies that emit large amounts of energy in the form of radio waves, X-rays, and gamma rays. This energy is produced by a supermassive black hole at the center of the galaxy. The black hole is surrounded by a disk of gas and dust that is being heated to very high temperatures. The heated gas and dust emit the energy that we observe. Dr. Brotherton then discussed the different types of active galaxies. There are two main types of active galaxies: Seyfert galaxies and quasars. Seyfert galaxies are active galaxies that are relatively close to Earth. Quasars are active galaxies that are very far away from Earth. Quasars are so far away that they appear as point sources of light, even through the largest telescopes. Dr. Brotherton explained that active galaxies can be used to study the early universe. Active galaxies are thought to be the progenitors of normal galaxies. By studying active galaxies, we can learn about the conditions that existed in the early universe and how galaxies evolved over time. Dr. Brotherton showed us some images of active galaxies that he had taken using the Hubble Space Telescope. The images showed the supermassive black holes at the centers of the galaxies and the disks of gas and dust that surround them. Dr. Brotherton concluded his talk by discussing the future of active galaxy research. He said that astronomers are currently using new telescopes and instruments to study active galaxies in more detail. He said that these studies are helping us to learn more about the early universe and the evolution of galaxies. Dr. Brotherton's talk was very informative and interesting. The audience asked many questions, and Dr. Brotherton answered them all patiently and thoroughly. The meeting was adjourned at 9:30 pm.

Bantam Lake (New York)

Bantam Lake is a spring-fed lake in Litchfield County, Connecticut. It is straddled by the border with Dutchess County, New York. The lake is 94 acres (38 ha) in size. It has a maximum depth of 53 feet (16 m). The lake is stocked with trout, bass, pickerel, and panfish. The lake is a popular spot for fishing, swimming, and boating. Bantam Lake is surrounded by a 1,515-acre (613 ha) state park. The park offers a variety of activities, including hiking, camping, picnicking, and fishing. The park is also home to a number of historic sites, including the 18th-century Litchfield County Courthouse and the 19th-century Litchfield County Jail. Bantam Lake is a popular destination for tourists and locals alike. It offers a beautiful setting for a variety of outdoor activities. The lake is also a great place to relax and enjoy the scenery.

Merdeka.com - Seorang pria berinisial HH (65) diamankan polisi Satreskrim Polres Metro Jakarta Barat bersama Polsek Kalideres, Selasa (16/11). Dia ditangkap usai mencabuli bocah perempuan berinisial Z (12). Kasat Reskrim Polres Metro Jakarta Barat, Kompol Joko Dwi Harsono mengatakan peristiwa ini terjadi pada Senin (15/11) malam. Saat itu korban diajak ke rumah pelaku di Jalan Semanan, RT 007/01, Kelurahan Semanan, Kecamatan Kalideres, Jakarta Barat yang tak jauh dari kediaman korban. "Pelaku memeluk serta meraba-raba korban. Setelah itu pelaku langsung mencabuli korban sementara kaki korban dipegangi oleh pelaku," kata Joko saat dihubungi, Rabu (17/11). Korban yang berhasil melepaskan diri dari pelaku langsung pulang ke rumah. Dia kemudian menceritakan kepada sang ibu soal perbuatan bejat yang dilakukan pelaku. "Mendengar pengakuan korban, ibu korban memutuskan untuk melaporkan kejadian tersebut ke Polsek Kalideres," jelas Joko. Di lokasi, polisi langsung menangkap pelaku. Setelah diinterogasi, pelaku mengakui semua perbuatannya. Dia juga mengaku sudah dua kali mencabuli korban sejak Oktober 2021. Pelaku dijerat Pasal 82 UU RI No 17 Tahun 2016 tentang Perlindungan Anak dengan ancaman pidana di atas lima tahun penjara. Not a bedbug
Ticks, Fleas and Bed Bugs all consume blood and must be inspected to identify the pest causing the infestation. If pests are found, the source of the infestation needs to be eradicated to prevent reinfestation. The first step in eradicating bed bugs is to identify their food source and nesting areas. Bed bugs are attracted to human blood and feces. They collect in areas where people spend time, such as bedrooms, living rooms and dens. Bed bugs can also nest in mattresses, box springs, furniture, picture frames, electrical appliances, and even clothing. Adult bed bugs are about the size of an apple seed and are reddish-brown in color. They are flat and have six legs. Bed bugs can infest any home or business. However, they are most commonly found in hotels, motels, dorms and apartments. Infestations can be difficult to detect because bed bugs do not live on their host. They feed for a short time and then return to their hiding places. Their bites often go unnoticed because they are small and do not cause much pain. If you think you have bed bugs, there are a few things you can do: Wash all of your bedding and clothing in hot water (at least 120 degrees Fahrenheit) and dry them on the highest heat setting. Vacuum your mattress, box spring, and carpets thoroughly. Seal any cracks or crevices in your furniture and walls where bed bugs might be hiding. Apply insecticide to areas where bed bugs are likely to be found, such as baseboards, furniture, and window frames. If you are unable to get rid of the bed bugs on your own, you can call a pest control company to help you. It is important to act quickly if you suspect you have a bed bug infestation. The sooner you act, the easier it will be to get rid of them.

trestles Trestles Beach is a surf spot along the Pacific coast of San Diego County, approximately 10 miles (16 km) south of San Clemente. The beach and campground is part of the San Onofre State Beach, a state park managed by the California Department of Parks and Recreation. The beach gets its name from the trestle bridge that used to traverse the area where the San Diego Freeway and Amtrak grade meet. The 120-foot (37 m) wooden trestle was built in 1929 and came to be known as the "Trestles." The bridge was torn down in the 1960s mid-century. Trestles is considered one of the best surf spots in Southern California. The waves are created by the rocky reefs and sandbars that line the coast. The reefs break the waves, creating long, clean waves that are perfect for surfing. The waves at Trestles range from mellow beginner waves to powerful waves that are onlyÈÄÇÂêàadvanced surfers. The best time to surf Trestles is during the summer months, when the waves are consistent. Winter swells can produce large, powerful waves, but these waves are only suitable for experienced surfers. Trestles is also a popular spot for bodyboarding, skimboarding, and stand-up paddleboarding. Trestles is home to a number of surf breaks, including Lower Trestles, Upper Trestles, and Cottons. Lower Trestles is the most popular break, and it is known for its long, clean waves. Upper Trestles is a more challenging break, with faster waves and more powerful barrels. Cottons is a smaller break, and it is best for beginner surfers. Trestles is a popular destination for surfers from all over the world. The beach is also a popular spot for camping, fishing, and picnicking. Trestle Beach Park is a 650-acre park that is located within the San Onofre State Beach. The park includes the Trestles surf breaks, as well as a campground, picnic areas, and hiking trails. Camping is available at the park, and there are also a number of restaurants and shops nearby.

Kerch

Kerch (Ukrainian: –ö–µ—Ä—á [k…õrt É]; Russian: –ö–µ—Ä—á—å [k ≤ert…ï]; Crimean Tatar: Keri√ß, pronounced [keÀàrit É]; Greek: ŒöŒµœÅŒ∫ŒØœÑŒπœÇ; Latin: Cercetis, Cercis, or Cercita) is a city of regional significance on the Kerch Peninsula in eastern Crimea. Population: 147,033 (2021 est.) Kerch is the administrative center of the Kerch Municipality, which is subdivided into the city itself and 10 rural councils with an area of 1,886 square kilometers (728 sq mi). The city is located on the Kerch Strait, separating Crimea from the Taman Peninsula in Krasnodar Krai, Russia. There are two bridges connecting the city with Krasnodar Krai: a road‚Äìrail bridge and a power bridge. Before the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine, ferries operated across the strait.

History

The earliest traces of human settlement in the area of the Kerch Peninsula date back to the 8th millennium BC. The area was settled by Cimmerians, Scythians, Greeks and Romans in ancient times. The Milesian Greeks of Miletus founded a trading city called Panticapaeum (Œ†Œ±ŒΩœÑŒπŒ∫Œ¨œÄŒ±ŒπŒøŒΩ) on the site of modern Kerch in the 7th century BC. Panticapaeum later became the capital of the Bosporan Kingdom. The city was destroyed by the Huns in the 4th century AD. Kerch was part of the Byzantine Empire from the 6th to the 10th centuries. It was then ruled by the Pechenegs, the Cumans, the Mongols, the Genoese and the Crimean Khanate. The Ottomans conquered the city in 1475. Kerch was annexed by the Russian Empire in 1774. It was renamed Kerch in 1790. The city was declared a free port in 1871. Kerch became a major industrial center in the late 19th century. During the Russian Civil War, Kerch was occupied by the Bolsheviks in 1918. The city was captured by the White Army in 1919, but it was retaken by the Bolsheviks in 1920. Kerch was occupied by Nazi Germany from 1941 to 1944. The city was heavily damaged during the war. After the war, Kerch was rebuilt and it became a major industrial and cultural center of the Crimean ASSR. Kerch became part of Ukraine in 1991 after the collapse of the Soviet Union. The city has suffered from a decline in population since the collapse of the Soviet Union, and its economy has been in decline since the Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation in 2014. On October 8, 2022, a large explosion on the Kerch Bridge connecting Russia and Crimea caused significant damage to the bridge. A section of the road bridge collapsed into the water, leaving only one lane open for traffic. The cause of the explosion is still under investigation, but Ukrainian officials have said that it was a deliberate attack.

Population

According to the 2001 Ukrainian census, the population of Kerch was 157,021. The majority of the population were Russians (74.2%), with Ukrainians (15.3%) and Crimean Tatars (6.1%) forming significant minorities. In 2014, after the annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation, the population of Kerch was estimated to be 146,675. A referendum was held in Crimea asking voters if they would support reunification with Russia. The referendum was condemned by the Ukrainian government and the vast majority of the international community. Historical population

Economy

The economy of Kerch is based on industry, port activities, and tourism. The city is home to a number of industrial enterprises, including a steel mill, a shipyard, and a fishing port. Kerch is also a major transportation hub, with a large port that handles cargo and passengers. The city is also a popular tourist destination, with a number of historical and cultural sites, including the Kerch Fortress, the Kerch Archaeological Museum, and the Kerch Shipyard. The Kerch Peninsula has several profitable economic sectors, most notably the transportation sector and mineral resource extraction. Some of the biggest mineral resources extracted in the region are limestone, sand, and clay. The region also has a large fishing industry. The most profitable fishing industry is the catch of sturgeon and its caviar. Kerch is also notable as the easternmost terminus of the North Crimean Canal. From the 1990s to the 2014 annexation of Crimea by Russia, the Port of Kerch was closed to all commercial and military vessels. It was reopened to marine traffic later that year, but was closed to non-Russian commercial and military vessels by the Russian Federation from March 2018.

Culture

Kerch is a cultural center of the Crimean Peninsula. The city is home to a number of museums, theaters, and art galleries. Kerch is also a popular tourist destination, with a number of historical and cultural sites. The main symbol of Kerch is Mount Mithridates, located in the heart of the city. On its top are the ruins of the ancient Greek city of Panticapaeum. The famous staircase of 423 steps, built in the 1830s, leads to the top of the mountain. Other popular tourist destinations in Kerch include the Kerch Fortress, the Kerch Archaeological Museum, and the Kerch Shipyard. The Kerch Fortress was built in the 18th century to protect the city from attack. The Kerch Archaeological Museum houses a collection of artifacts from the ancient Greek, Scythian, and Roman civilizations. The Kerch Shipyard is a historic shipyard that has been in operation since the 18th century. Kerch is also home to a number of cultural festivals and events throughout the year. One of the most popular festivals is the Kerch International Maritime Festival, which is held every year in July. The festival features a variety of maritime-themed events, including boat races, regattas, and concerts.

Transportation

Kerch is a major transportation hub, with a large port that handles cargo and passengers. The city is also a major road and rail junction. The Kerch Port is one of the largest ports in the Black Sea. It handles a variety of cargo, including oil, grain, and metals. The port is also a major passenger port, with ferries connecting Kerch to other cities in Crimea and Russia. Kerch is also a major road and rail junction. The M17 highway connects Kerch to Simferopol, the capital of Crimea. The Kerch-Tavrida Highway, which connects Simferopol to Krasnodar in Russia, is currently under construction. The city is also served by a number of railway lines, including the Kerch-Simferopol line and the Kerch-Krasnodar line. The Kerch Peninsula is connected to the Taman Peninsula in Krasnodar Krai, Russia, by two bridges: a road‚Äìrail bridge and a power bridge. The Kerch Bridge is a 19-kilometer (12 mi) long bridge that was completed in 2018. The bridge is the longest bridge in Europe.

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\User;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class UserController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        $users = User::all();
        return view('users.index', compact('users'));
    }

    public function create()
    {
        return view('users.create');
    }

    public function store(Request $request)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'name' => 'required',
            'email' => 'required|email',
            'password' => 'required|min:6',
        ]);

        $user = User::create([
            'name' => $request->name,
            'email' => $request->email,
            'password' => bcrypt($request->password),
        ]);
        storeImage($request->file('image'), 'user', $user->id);

        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User created successfully.');
    }

    public function edit(User $user)
    {
        return view('users.edit', compact('user'));
    }

    public function update(Request $request, User $user)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'name' => 'required',
            'email' => 'required|email',
            'password' => 'required|min:6',
        ]);

        $user->update([
            'name' => $request->name,
            'email' => $request->email,
            'password' => bcrypt($request->password),
        ]);
        storeImage($request->file('image'), 'user', $user->id);
        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User updated successfully.');
    }

    public function destroy(User $user)
    {
        $user->delete();
        deleteAllImages('user', $user->id);
        return redirect('users')->with('success', 'User deleted successfully.');
    }
}

#!/usr/bin/env python


"""Runs all types of tests for the project."""

import argparse
import os

import cpp_lint
import env_setup
import out_of_tree_build
import regressiontest
import unittests


def main() -> None:
  """Parses command line arguments and runs the tests selected by the user."""

  parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
      description=(
          'Runs all types of tests for the project. '
          'If no arguments are provided, only the basic tests are run.'))
  parser.add_argument(
      '-c',
      '--cpplint',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'Run cpplint_unittest/cpplint_test on the source code, checking the '
          'format.'))

  parser.add_argument(
      '-u',
      '--unittests',
      action='store_true',
      help='Run the unittests for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-r',
      '--regressiontest',
      action='store_true',
      help='Run regression tests for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-i',
      '--interactive',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'If set, will run the interactive regression tests (this will require '
          'a GUI).'))

  parser.add_argument(
      '-b',
      '--build',
      action='store_true',
      help='Build the artifacts for the project.')

  parser.add_argument(
      '-a',
      '--all',
      action='store_true',
      help=(
          'Run all of the tests and build artifacts for the project, including '
          'build performance tests.'))

  args = parser.parse_args()

  env_setup.setup_env()

  if not args.build and not args.cpplint and not args.unittests and not args.regressiontest:
    args.build = True
    args.unittests = True
    args.cpplint = True
    args.regressiontest = True

  if args.all:
    args.build = True
    args.cpplint = True
    args.unittests = True
    args.regressiontest = True

  if args.build:
    out_of_tree_build.build()

  if args.unittests:
    unittests.run()

  if args.cpplint:
    cpp_lint.run_cpplint()

  if args.regressiontest:
    regressiontest.run(args.interactive)


if __name__ == '__main__':
  main()

Neuraxial drug administration. Cocaine can readily cross the blood-brain barrier when administered either systemically (IV or intranasally) or locally (intrathecally). The total concentration of cocaine in brain is a composite of both inherent regional concentration differences and relative contribution of blood versus neuraxial drug appearance. After systemic administration of 200 mg IV, the concentration of cocaine in CSF is only about 10% that of the concentration in blood. In contrast, as much as 25% of the administered dose can be measured in CSF following a 5-mg intrathecal injection. Although much of the intrathecal dose leaks into the systemic circulation, local concentrations remain high for over 8 hours. Systemic cocaine can also be detected in the spinal cord, albeit at lower concentrations than cerebrocortical concentrations. Cardiovascular effects. Cocaine increases mean blood pressure, heart rate, and cardiac output. These effects are due to inhibition of norepinephrine reuptake, resulting in enhanced sympathetic outflow. Intrathecal cocaine may be useful to treat hypotension after spinal anesthesia, although this application has been limited by variable data and potential for severe toxicity. Respiratory effects. Cocaine is a local anesthetic of the mucous membranes and can cause numbness, burning, and other untoward sensations of the nose, sinuses, and throat. In moderate to high doses, cocaine is a respiratory stimulant that increases respiratory rate and tidal volume. However, very high doses can paralyze the muscles of respiration and may contribute to death from cocaine overdose. Gastrointestinal effects. Systemic cocaine can cause nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain as a result of enhancement of sympathetic outflow. Cocaine appears to inhibit appetite and has been used to promote weight loss, although this practice has been supplanted by safer centrally acting agents that promote satiety. Central nervous system effects. In moderate doses, cocaine causes excitement, euphoria, confidence, and sociability. It can also impair judgment and decision-making capacities and may induce paranoia. Cocaine decreases the sensation of fatigue and hunger but may also induce anxiety and seizures. In chronic users, cocaine may lead to psychosis. Cocaine users often become dependent on the drug and experience depression, fatigue, and irritability when the drug is stopped. Topical effects. Cocaine is useful as a topical anesthetic on mucous membranes owing to its ability to block sodium channels and prevent the initiation and propagation of action potentials. The regional anesthetic properties of cocaine persist after local administration for 15 to 30 minutes. As a local anesthetic, cocaine is approximately equal in potency to lidocaine and ropivacaine but exhibits a shorter duration of action. Cocaine is also a potent vasoconstrictor, and local administration can result in ischemia. As a result, cocaine is used rarely as a local anesthetic and is most commonly used topically as a nasal decongestant. Pupillary effects. Cocaine is a sympathomimetic and can cause pupillary dilation in a dose- and route-dependent manner. Severe acute toxicity can cause pupils to dilate maximally or to remain fixed and dilated as a result of death of iris sphincter muscles from ischemia. Antidotes. There are no specific antidotes for cocaine overdose. Treatment is supportive and includes the use of benzodiazepines to control seizures, nicardipine to reduce blood pressure, and propofol for sedation if intubation is necessary.

Merdeka.com - Seorang bocah laki-laki berusia 11 tahun dari North Carolina, Amerika Serikat, bunuh diri setelah dituduh membobol mobil oleh beberapa polisi. Polisi tersebut menuduh tanpa bukti dan menggeledahnya secara tak patut. Menurut laporan Time, bocah tersebut, bernama Jaheim McMillan, bunuh diri pada 28 November lalu di kamarnya. Sebelumnya, ia bertemu dengan polisi setempat pada 21 Oktober. Washington Post melaporkan, polisi mendapatkan laporan dari seorang pekerja yang mengatakan ia melihat seorang Jaheim McMillan sedang mengobrak-abrik sebuah mobil yang terparkir di luar gedung apartemen. Dari empat petugas polisi yang tiba di lokasi, seorang yang paling ngotot menuduhnya dan memintanya menunjukkan isi tasnya. Jaheim menuruti permintaan polisi tersebut dan menunjukkan isi tasnya. Namun, polisi tersebut tetap menuduhnya dan bahkan menggeledah tasnya tanpa meminta izin. Polisi menemukan sebuah sarung tangan di dalam tas Jaheim, dan itu langsung disebut-sebut sebagai barang bukti. Polisi tersebut mengatakan sarung tangan adalah barang bukti. "Pencuri memakai sarung tangan, jadi menurutmu apa yang akan dilakukan seorang pencuri di dalam mobil? Mencari sesuatu untuk dicuri," kata polisi tersebut. Jaheim terus-menerus membantah tuduhan tersebut. Ia mengatakan ia hanya mengambil sebuah kotak A&W dari temannya dan memasukkannya ke dalam tasnya. Setelah itu ia duduk di sebuah taman dekat gedung apartemen. Seorang saksi mengatakan kepada Time dia melihat Jaheim sedang mengambil sesuatu dari mobil, namun ia tidak melihat Jaheim masuk ke dalam mobil. Saksi tersebut mengonfirmasi pernyataan Jaheim bahwa ia sedang duduk di taman. Polisi juga menuduhnya telah merampok sebuah toko pada beberapa minggu sebelumnya. Jaheim tetap menampik tuduhan tersebut dan mengatakan ia ada di luar kota ketika perampokan terjadi. Namun, polisi tidak mempercayainya dan memintanya menunjukkannya kata sandi ponselnya untuk memeriksa lokasinya saat kejadian. Jaheim pun terpaksa menuruti permintaan polisi tersebut. Jaheim pulang ke rumah ibunya dalam keadaan sangat marah. Ia mengaku sangat marah kepada polisi yang menuduhnya melakukan hal-hal yang tidak dilakukannya. Jaheim tidak mau menandatangani surat pelanggaran apa pun dari polisi karena ia merasa tidak melakukan kejahatan. Seminggu setelah bertemu dengan polisi, Jaheim diwinterview oleh petugas layanan perlindungan anak. Ia menceritakan semua yang terjadi pada hari itu kepada petugas tersebut. Menurut pengakuan ibu Jaheim, putranya terlihat sangat terganggu sejak kejadian itu. Jaheim tidak mau keluar rumah dan memilih untuk mengurung diri di kamarnya. Ia menolak pergi sekolah dan tidak mau bertemu dengan siapa pun. Pada tanggal 28 November, ibu Jaheim menemukannya tewas bunuh diri di kamarnya. "Saya melihat banyak anak yang mendapat masalah, tapi ini adalah tuduhan palsu," kata Tiffany McMillan, ibu Jaheim. Ia mengatakan, meskipun Jaheim memiliki masalah perilaku, ia tidak pernah terlibat masalah dengan hukum sebelumnya. Pengacara keluarga Jaheim saat ini sedang berusaha untuk mengajukan gugatan kepada departemen kepolisian setempat. Menurut mereka, polisi tidak memiliki bukti yang cukup untuk menuduh Jaheim melakukan kejahatan. Mereka juga mengatakan polisi seharusnya tidak menggeledah tas Jaheim tanpa izin. Kepala polisi kota Dunn, Larry Smith, mengatakan polisi yang menangani kasus Jaheim telah diskorsing sampai waktu yang tidak ditentukan. **6. Function that sorts the array in ascending order based on the value of the "hours" key.**

```python
def sort_by_hours_ascending(array):
  """
  Sorts the array in ascending order based on the value of the "hours" key.

  Args:
    array: The array to sort.

  Returns:
    The sorted array.
  """

  return sorted(array, key=lambda x: x["hours"])
```

A Climate, Energy and Security (CES) Task Force of the United States Congress recently issued a report that highlights sustainable development and the need for additional authorization of funds for the State Department's international energy and climate programs. In the report, the Task Force calls for "accelerated global deployment of solar, wind, and other clean energy technologies for electricity generation, transportation, heating and cooling of buildings, and industrial processes." The Task Force also calls for "increased support for the Clean Technology Fund" (CTF).

The CTF is a joint trust administered by the World Bank and managed by a multilateral interim trustee composed of representatives from all donor countries. The CTF provides financial and technical assistance to developing countries "to promote energy access, energy efficiency, and renewable energy" through investments and technical assistance in renewable energy, energy efficiency, and sustainable transportation. The United States made three contributions to the CTF in 2009 and 2010, totaling US$540 million, and has pledged an additional US$120 million in 2013. The CTF has since been capitalized with US$5.1 billion by 18 bilateral donors and has supported 29 projects in 23 countries.

In May 2013, President Obama announced a new U.S.-Africa Clean Energy Finance Initiative that is intended to raise US$2 billion in combined private and public sector financing to support renewable and clean energy generation and access in sub-Saharan Africa. As part of the initiative, the United States has pledged US$120 million to the CTF.

ROBERT BAKER OBITUARY

BAKER, Robert "Bob" Robert "Bob" Baker, born January 5, 1940 in Lindsay, California, passed away peacefully at the age of 81 on December 14, 2021 at his home in Chico, surrounded by his loving family. Those who knew Bob will remember him for his love of his family, friends, his Corvette, dancing, and history. He had a passion for travel and enjoyed exploring different places and learning about their cultures. Bob was also known for his love of corny jokes, his quick wit, and his infectious laugh. Bob is survived by his beloved wife of 61 years, Gail Baker; son, Ken Baker (Jennifer) of York, South Carolina; daughter, Kristen Baker of Sacramento, California; three grandchildren, Victoria, Morgan, and Alex; and numerous other family and friends. Bob was preceded in death by his parents, Johnny and Virginia Baker and his brother, Joe Baker. Per Bob's request there will be no services held. In lieu of flowers, memorial contributions can be made to the charity of the donor's choice. Condolences can be sent to the family online at: www.brusiefh.com

Donald Sterling, the former owner of the Los Angeles Clippers, died at the age of 83.

Sterling died Tuesday at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles, his wife, Shelly Sterling, said in a statement. No cause of death was given.

‚ÄúHe was a kind and generous man who loved his family and friends,‚Äù Shelly Sterling said. ‚ÄúHe will be greatly missed.‚Äù

Sterling owned the Clippers for more than 30 years, but his tenure was marred by controversy. In 2014, he was recorded making racist remarks about African Americans, which led to him being banned from the NBA for life. He was also forced to sell the team, which was purchased by Steve Ballmer for $2 billion.

Sterling‚Äôs death comes just weeks after the death of his wife, Shelly. She died on January 26 at the age of 83.

Sterling is survived by his two children, Scott and Joanna.

practicalrat writes: The problem I ran into was that I couldn't get anything to bind to the USB port. I tried a USB keyboard, a USB mouse, a USB flash drive, and a USB Ethernet adapter. Nothing showed up in the menus. No devices, no drivers. The USB ports did provide power - external HDDs worked just fine. I tried this on Ubuntu 20.04 with kernel 5.13.0-39-generic and on Ubuntu 22.04 with kernel 5.15.0-47-generic. I tried adding pci=nomsi to the kernel boot options. No dice. I took the laptop apart and reseated the WiFi/Bluetooth module. No dice. I installed Windows and all the USB ports worked fine. I also tried booting a live Arch Linux USB and ran into the same problem. I'm at my wit's end. I would really like to get USB working on this laptop with Linux.
I've found a solution for this. In the BIOS/UEFI settings, there is a setting called "USB Controller Mode". This setting is set to "AHCI" by default. Change this setting to "XHCI". After doing this, USB devices will start working in Linux. Note: This setting does not affect the Windows installation in any way. Windows will still boot and work normally. Hope this helps!

On Feb. 13th, the president of the African Development Bank (AfDB), Akinwumi Adesina, met with the president of the Export-Import Bank of China (China Exim), Hu Xiaolian. The two organizations signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) to strengthen their partnership in co-financing projects in Africa. The MOU covers infrastructure, agriculture, clean energy, digitalization and the private sector in particular.

Analysis

The partnership is expected to increase the resources available to fund Africa's long-term economic and social development. The AfDB stated that it will use its experience in understanding Africa's development environment to screen and select projects for co-financing, while China Exim will bring its funding capacity, long-term credit facilities and strong global presence to the table. The agreement reflects China's commitment to supporting African countries' economic and social development as well as the increasing importance of the China-Africa economic relationship in recent years. 

China has become Africa's largest trading partner, and its share in Africa's total trade increased from 11% in 2000 to 23% in 2017. China also became a major investor in Africa, with Chinese foreign direct investment (FDI) in Africa increasing from US$75m in 2003 to US$40bn in 2017, accounting for about 20% of total FDI in Africa. 

One of the key areas of cooperation between China and Africa has been in infrastructure development. China Exim has been a major financier of infrastructure projects in Africa, such as the Ethiopia-Djibouti Railway, the Mombasa Standard Gauge Railway, and the new international terminal at Ngqura Port in South Africa. The bank has also provided financing for projects in the energy sector, such as the construction of the Grand Inga Dam in the Democratic Republic of Congo, which will be the largest hydroelectric power plant in the world when it is completed.

The agreement between the AfDB and China Exim is likely to further boost China-Africa cooperation in infrastructure development. The two institutions will work together to identify and co-finance projects that will have a positive impact on economic growth and social development in Africa. They will also work to promote the use of innovative financing mechanisms, such as public-private partnerships, to attract private sector investment in infrastructure projects.

The partnership between the AfDB and China Exim is also expected to help promote the development of Africa's private sector. The AfDB and China Exim will work together to provide financial and technical support to African businesses, and to promote the participation of African businesses in regional and global value chains. They will also work to improve the investment climate in Africa, and to encourage Chinese companies to invest in Africa.

Impact on the forecast

The deal between the AfDB and China Exim is positive for our forecast for African economic growth. The additional resources that will be available for infrastructure development and private sector development will help to boost economic growth over the next few years. The deal is also positive for our forecast for China's economic growth, as it will help to boost exports and create jobs in China.

Our current forecast for Africa's real GDP growth is 3.8% in 2021 and 4.1% in 2022. We expect the deal between the AfDB and China Exim to support stronger growth in African economies. We may revise up our growth forecast for Africa in the near future.

Terrain is the only source of data that we can use to make decisions about our planet's future. It is the foundation for all environmental decision-making, from land use planning to climate change adaptation.

Terrain data is used to:

* Plan for and respond to natural hazards, such as floods, droughts, and wildfires
* Manage water resources, such as rivers, lakes, and aquifers
* Protect and restore ecosystems, such as forests, wetlands, and coral reefs
* Plan for and develop sustainable land use practices, such as agriculture, forestry, and mining
* Adapt to climate change, such as sea level rise and changes in precipitation patterns

Terrain data is essential for understanding the Earth's surface and how it is changing over time. It helps us to make informed decisions about how to use and manage our natural resources and how to adapt to the impacts of climate change.

There are many different ways to collect terrain data. Some of the most common methods include:

* Aerial photography
* Satellite imagery
* Lidar (Light Detection and Ranging)
* Ground-based surveys

Once terrain data has been collected, it can be used to create a variety of different products, such as:

* Topographic maps
* Digital elevation models (DEMs)
* Land use maps
* Watershed boundary maps
* Flood hazard maps

Terrain data is a valuable resource for a variety of decision-makers, including:

* Government agencies
* Land use planners
* Environmental scientists
* Engineers
* Architects
* Developers
* Homeowners

Terrain data can help us to make better decisions about how to use and manage our natural resources and how to adapt to the impacts of climate change.

Abstract

The possibility of using two interconnected sources of light, specifically a conventional laser and a laser diode with mutually perpendicular polarization, to excite two photon transitions in an atomic system is analyzed. The matrix elements of the Hamiltonian of the interaction of atoms with the radiation field in the second order of perturbation theory are calculated. Expressions are obtained for the probabilities of the corresponding two-photon transitions. It is shown that the two-photon excitation transitions occur more efficiently at certain ratios of the intensities of two laser radiators, which are calculated for each transition.

The castle is built of masonry and it is in good condition.

[multimodal]<start_of_image>Zoonosis is any disease or infection that is transmissible from animals to humans. This can occur directly or indirectly. Direct zoonosis occurs when the infectious agent is transmitted from an animal to a human, such as through a bite, scratch, or contact with the animal's saliva, blood, or other bodily fluids. Indirect zoonosis occurs when the infectious agent is transmitted from an animal to a human through an intermediate host, such as a mosquito, tick, or flea.

There are many different types of zoonoses, including:

* Bacterial infections, such as salmonella, E. coli, and Lyme disease
* Viral infections, such as rabies, flu, and HIV
* Parasitic infections, such as malaria, hookworm, and tapeworm
* Fungal infections, such as ringworm and histoplasmosis

Zoonoses can cause a wide range of symptoms, depending on the specific infection. Some zoonoses can be mild, while others can be serious or even fatal.

Zoonoses are a public health concern because they can be transmitted from animals to humans, and they can cause a variety of diseases. As a result, it is important to take steps to prevent the spread of zoonoses. These steps include:

* Washing hands frequently with soap and water
* Avoiding contact with animals that are sick or appear to be sick
* Cooking meat and fish thoroughly
* Using insect repellent and wearing protective clothing when in areas where there are mosquitoes, ticks, or fleas
* Getting vaccinated against certain zoonoses, such as rabies and flu

Zoonoses are a serious public health concern, but they can be prevented. By taking steps to prevent the spread of zoonoses, we can help to keep ourselves and our loved ones healthy.

Here are some tips for investing in the stock market during a bull market rally:

* Choose strong stocks. Not all stocks will benefit from a bull market rally. Focus on companies with strong fundamentals, such as earnings growth and a strong balance sheet.

 * When the result of an expression is indeterminate, such as the square

 * NaN can be tested using the JavaScript isNaN() function.

console.log(Math.sqrt(-4)); // NaN

console.log(isNaN('hello')); // true
console.log(isNaN(10)); // false

She said, ‚ÄúI give you the right to go ahead and do it.‚Äù

A close friend, Victoria Kleber, did just that. Kleber, 27, went ahead and implanted one of the first batches of the AlloStem system ‚Äî made entirely from donor tissue ‚Äî into a 68-year-old patient with heart failure. The procedure took place in February at the Texas Heart Institute in Houston.

The patient did well in the short term, Kleber said.

‚ÄúThe heart got smaller, the ejection fraction went up,‚Äù she said, meaning the heart performed better and was able to pump more blood. ‚ÄúBut we couldn‚Äôt tell how much was patient variation and how much was the treatment.‚Äù

At the six-month follow-up, the patient had died, though not from any problem stemming from the treatment, Kleber said.

The treatment is still experimental, and scientists don‚Äôt yet know whether it could help patients in the long term. The idea behind AlloStem is to replace damaged heart tissue with healthy tissue that can grow and function properly.

In theory, it‚Äôs a good concept, said Dr. Charles Murry, director of the Institute for Stem Cell and Regenerative Medicine at the University of Washington. But it‚Äôs been difficult to develop safe and effective stem cell treatments for heart disease, he added.

‚ÄúThe heart is a ridiculously complex organ,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs got billions of cells in it, it‚Äôs got all sorts of different compartments. And it‚Äôs very difficult to create a stem cell-based intervention that will regenerate all of the different types of cells you need to make the heart work properly.‚Äù

Researchers have been trying to develop stem cell therapies for heart disease for more than two decades. Several clinical trials have shown that injecting stem cells into the heart can improve cardiac function, but the results have been inconsistent. In some cases, the stem cells have died or formed tumors.

AlloStem‚Äôs technology uses a different approach. Instead of injecting stem cells directly into the heart, the system is designed to create a scaffold that supports the growth of new heart tissue. The scaffold is made from a biocompatible material that is seeded with stem cells. The stem cells are then stimulated to differentiate into cardiomyocytes, the cells that make up the heart muscle.

In laboratory tests, AlloStem‚Äôs system has been shown to create functional heart tissue that can contract and pump blood. The system has also been shown to be safe in animal studies.

Kleber said the AlloStem system has the potential to be a major breakthrough in the treatment of heart disease. If the system is successful, it could offer a new way to treat patients who are currently ineligible for heart transplantation.

‚ÄúWe‚Äôd be able to offer this treatment to people who are too old or too sick for surgery,‚Äù she said. ‚ÄúIt would be a game-changer.‚Äù

Researchers are still conducting clinical trials to evaluate the safety and efficacy of AlloStem‚Äôs system. If the trials are successful, the system could be approved for clinical use within the next few years.

SUBANG-Kepala Badan Kesatuan Bangsa dan Politik (Kesbangpol) Kabupaten Subang, H. Cecep Supriatin menyampaikan bahwa pendidikan politik adalah salah satu upaya yang dilakukan untuk mengajarkan kepada warga negara mengenai hak dan kewajiban mereka sebagai warga negara. ‚ÄúPendidikan politik ini sangat penting untuk dilakukan, karena dapat menciptakan warga negara yang aktif dan sadar akan hak dan kewajibannya sebagai warga negara,‚Äù kata Cecep. Selain itu, lanjut Cecep, pendidikan politik juga dapat menumbuhkan kesadaran masyarakat dalam berpartisipasi aktif dalam pembangunan daerah. ‚ÄúSaya berharap, dengan pendidikan politik ini masyarakat Subang semakin sadar dan aktif dalam berpartisipasi aktif membangun daerahnya,‚Äù ujarnya. Cecep menuturkan, bahwa salah satu upaya Pemkab Subang untuk meningkatkan pendidikan politik di masyarakat, yakni dengan melakukan berbagai kegiatan, seperti pelatihan kepemimpinan pemuda, pelatihan kader partai politik, dan diskusi-diskusi politik. Selain itu, Pemkab Subang juga telah membentuk Pusat Kajian Pancasila dan Demokrasi (PKPD) di Universitas Subang. ‚ÄúPKPD ini merupakan salah satu upaya Pemkab Subang untuk meningkatkan kualitas pendidikan politik di masyarakat,‚Äù terangnya. The International Tee Ball Association and Tee Ball Canada have agreed to merge.

The organizations said Thursday the merger will take place Jan. 1. They hope to increase their combined membership of youth and adult players to 2 million by 2020.

"We are excited to join forces with ITBA and look forward to working with their team of volunteers, staff and supporters to further grow and promote tee ball for all," Tee Ball Canada president Ray Aduckiewicz said in a statement.

"ITBA is thrilled to have Tee Ball Canada as the newest member of our organization," James Wilson, president of the International Tee Ball Association, said in a statement. "Canada has been a partner with ITBA for many years and we are looking forward to having them now as an integral part of our organization."

Tee ball is a youth team sport similar to baseball but with some differences. The ball is placed on a tee instead of being pitched, and players use a bat that is shorter and wider than a baseball bat. The bases are also closer together.

Players must be 4 or 5 years old.

DB2 Data Propagation for File Transfer Protocol (FTP) Overview

DB2¬Æ Data Propagation for File Transfer Protocol (FTP) is an MQ Connect extension that provides unidirectional replication of data from DB2 for z/OS¬Æ to target systems through FTP. Data propagation is a high-performance, low-latency, change data capture (CDC) technology that is used to replicate data to multiple destinations in near real time, using the DB2 CDC subsystem to capture changes. Data propagation can significantly reduce the time required to refresh data and can offer multiple benefits, including: * Reduced bandwidth requirements * Increased data security * Improved data reliability and operational efficiency * Optimized resource utilization In this solution, DB2 Data Propagation for FTP is used to replicate data, including both table and LOB data, from a source system to target systems that are located on different servers or in different data centers that are connected through FTP. The data propagation technology includes a high-performance data transfer engine that optimizes data transmission, minimizes network overhead, and ensures faster replication. DB2 for z/OS

DB2 for z/OS is an enterprise-class relational database management system that provides a wide range of capabilities for managing and processing business data, including: * Transaction processing * Data warehousing * Business intelligence * Advanced analytics

MQ Connect

MQ Connect is a suite of products that provides a comprehensive set of capabilities for connecting applications, data, and services across hybrid infrastructures. MQ Connect includes the following components: * MQ Connection Manager (MCM): A lightweight connectivity solution that provides a secure and reliable way to connect applications to messaging systems. * MQ Messaging Gateway (MMG): A high-performance messaging gateway that enables applications to send and receive messages using a variety of protocols, such as JMS, AMQP, MQTT, and WebSockets. * MQ Telemetry Transport (MQTT) Gateway (MQGW): Provides support for the MQTT protocol, which is a popular connectivity protocol for IoT devices and applications. * MQ Capture: A change data capture solution that enables the replication of data from source systems to target systems in near real time. * MQ Managed File Transfer (MFT): A secure, enterprise-grade file transfer solution that supports a wide range of protocols and provides advanced file transfer capabilities, such as file compression, encryption, and audit logging.

IBM¬Æ Z¬Æ Communications Server (ZCS) for File Transfer Protocol (FTP)

MQ Capture CDC Plugin for DB2 for z/OS

The MQ Capture CDC Plugin for DB2 for z/OS is a software component that enables MQ Capture to capture changes from DB2 for z/OS tables and replicate the changes to target systems.

Source and target systems

The source system is the system that contains the data that will be replicated to the target systems. The target systems are the systems that will receive and store the replicated data. In this solution, the source system is a DB2 for z/OS system, and the target systems can be a variety of systems, such as DB2 for z/OS, DB2 for Linux, UNIX and Windows, or a system that uses a different database, such as Oracle, Microsoft SQL Server, or SAP Hana.

FTP server

Benefits of DB2 Data Propagation for FTP

DB2 Data Propagation for FTP provides the following benefits: * High performance and low latency: The data propagation technology includes a high-performance data transfer engine that optimizes data transmission, minimizes network overhead, and ensures faster replication. * Reduced bandwidth requirements: Data propagation uses an efficient data transfer format that reduces the amount of data that is transferred over the network. * Increased data security: Data propagation uses secure protocols to transfer data between the source and target systems. * Improved data reliability and operational efficiency: Data propagation provides reliable data delivery and can help to improve operational efficiency by reducing the time required to refresh data. * Optimized resource utilization: Data propagation can help to optimize resource utilization by reducing the load on the source system and the target systems.

Use cases for DB2 Data Propagation for FTP

DB2 Data Propagation for FTP can be used in a variety of scenarios, including: * Data warehousing: Data propagation can be used to replicate data from a DB2 for z/OS system to a data warehouse for reporting and analysis. * Business intelligence: Data propagation can be used to replicate data from a DB2 for z/OS system to a business intelligence platform for reporting and analysis. * Application integration: Data propagation can be used to replicate data from a DB2 for z/OS system to other applications for use in various business processes. * Disaster recovery: Data propagation can be used to replicate data from a DB2 for z/OS system to a disaster recovery site for protection against data loss. * Data migration: Data propagation can be used to migrate data from a DB2 for z/OS system to a different system, such as a DB2 for Linux, UNIX and Windows system, a DB2 for z/OS system on a different server, or a system that uses a different database.

Using PowerShell to pause a Microsoft Project Web Application 2017 session

I am trying to pause a Microsoft Project Web Application 2017 user session. I have a script that has the ability to start and stop sessions, but I can't seem to find how to pause a session. I have included the script that I currently use and all possible parameters that I could find in the documentation, but none of these seem to work. Param( $pwaURL, $userName, [Switch]$start, [Switch]$stop, [Switch]$pause, [Switch]$resume ) $pwa = New-Object Microsoft.ProjectServer.Client.ProjectContext($pwaURL) $pwa.Credentials = Get-Credential -UserName $userName if ($start) { Write-Output "Starting session..." $session = $pwa.CurrentSession $session.Start() Write-Output "Session started." } if ($stop) { Write-Output "Stopping session..." $session = $pwa.CurrentSession $session.Stop() Write-Output "Session stopped." } if ($pause) { Write-Output "Pausing session..." $session = $pwa.CurrentSession $session.Pause() Write-Output "Session paused." } if ($resume) { Write-Output "Resuming session..." $session = $pwa.CurrentSession $session.Resume() Write-Output "Session resumed." } [Answer 1] Unfortunately, pausing a session is not a feature available to the PWA API.

You can always get better in school. You can never get better at life.
I guess in a way this is true because school educates you and tries to teach you to be productive in life.
School also misses a lot of life lessons, and does little to prepare people for the real world.
I kinda hate this argument. Sure you can get better at things in school, but school subjects aren't nearly as important as life lessons. How many people would you say could balance a checkbook or change the oil in their car compared to how many people can solve for x in an equation? The problem with our education system is that it doesn't teach students how to be successful in life.
Perhaps, but school is designed to teach you things you otherwise would not learn on your own or in life but you need to know to be successful in the real world. Things like math, science, economics, etc. These aren't things you can easily learn on your own or you'd need to dedicate years to teaching yourself.
Life isn't about "getting better." Id say it's more about balance and maintenance.

I‚Äôve owned multiple Z31s over the years, and a rough idle is normally caused by a vacuum leak. If you have a vacuum leak, it could also cause your air fuel ratio to be off which will cause a rough idle. If you‚Äôre not sure where to start looking for a vacuum leak, you can use a can of carb cleaner. Just spray it around hoses, fittings, and gaskets while the car is running and listen for a change in idle. Make sure you do this in a well ventilated area, and be careful not to spray the carb cleaner near hot exhaust. It‚Äôs also a good idea to check your spark plugs and wires.
There are some other things that could cause a rough idle, but they‚Äôre less common. Here are a few things I would check:
1. Check all your vacuum lines for leaks.
2. Check your idle air control valve (IAC).
3. Check your throttle position sensor (TPS).
4. Check your coolant temperature sensor (CTS).
5. Check your fuel pressure regulator (FPR).
6. Clean your throttle body and intake manifold.
